No, fuck you. That is a copout. If stuff isn't consistent with how people act in real life, you need to specify that. Internal consistency is what matters in a setting above all else, and you need to clearly define how it does and does not conform to real life if you're going to make large departures in human behaviors. Humans empathize a lot more than most people would care to admit, and despite being base, tribal creatures we still are able to connect with people that aren't like us at all. In a setting with anthros that have been there a while, affinity and animosity would be developed around geography and history like they are in real life.
